org.ObjectLayout

Class PrimitiveLongArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ObjectLayout.AbstractPrimitiveArray
      • org.ObjectLayout.PrimitiveLongArray

  • public class PrimitiveLongArray
extends AbstractPrimitiveArray
    A subclassable array of longs. PrimitiveLongArray is designed with semantics specifically chosen and restricted such that a "flat" memory layout of the implemented data structure would be possible on optimizing JVMs. While fully functional on all JVM implementation (of Java SE 6 and above), the semantics are such that a JVM may transparently optimise the implementation to provide a compact contiguous layout that facilitates dead-reckoning (as opposed to de-referenced) access to elements
